29/05/2011
PRISTINA, Kosovo -- Visiting EU foreign policy chief Catherine Ashton told Kosovo officials on Friday (May 27th) that the rule of law is crucial to the country's future. 
After talks with Prime Minister Hashim Thaci in Prizren, she said that they discussed Kosovo's EU bid and visa liberalisation issues. 
Ashton voiced support for the work of the EU Rule of Law mission in Kosovo and she invited Thaci to visit Brussels. 
He reiterated that Kosovo institutions are doing their best to implement all democratic criteria in politics, legislation and the economy in order to speed up potential European integration. 
(Radio Free Europe, VOA - 27/05/11)
